Incident.Summary: Vehicle was stopped for moving violations. Upon contact with the driver, the odor of an alcoholic beverage was detected and clear signs of intoxication was observed. Driver refused SFST's and was arrested for DUI/DWI.

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText:
In-Car camera and body worn camera operational H-13.

Defendant: Norwood, Christel Ebony

Date of Birth: 02/22/1976

Time of arrest: 0303 hours

Location: Altamont Place at Billingsley Road, White Plains, Charles County, Maryland, 20695.

Virginia driver's license: A61486271

DUI#: 23-189

2nd DUI

CERTIFICATES AND TRAINING

*Trained in administering Standardized Field Sobriety Tests through the Maryland State Police.

*Trained in Advanced Roadside Impaired Driving Enforcement through Charles County Sheriff's Office.

*Trained in Crisis Intervention Team through Calvert County Sheriff’s Office.

NARRATIVE/ VEHICLE IN MOTION (PHASE 1):

On 11/08/2023 at approximately 0254 hours, I, Tpr. Tripp with the Maryland State Police La Plata Barrack “H” was on patrol in lane one, southbound Route 301 in the area of Smallwood Drive, Waldorf, Charles County, Maryland. I observed a white BMW X5, bearing Virginia registration TPB1691 in lane two changing lanes unsafely on southbound Route 301 in the area of Smallwood Drive, Waldorf, Charles County, Maryland 20603. The white BMW crossed over into the right shoulder approximately one tires length for three seconds before merging back into lane two. The white BMW merges into lane one and cross over into lane two approximately two tires length for three seconds before merging back into lane one. I observed the vehicle cross into the lane two (nearly colliding into a white SUV) approximately two tires length for five seconds before merging back into lane one. The white BMW then merges onto the right turn lane and turns onto Altamont Place. I then activate my emergency equipment and stopped the vehicle in lane one at Altamont Place at Billingsley Road, White Plains, Charles County, Maryland, 20695.


PERSONAL CONTACT (PHASE 2):

Once I approached the vehicle, the driver did not roll down the window. I knocked on the driver side window advising her to roll down the window. Once the driver complied, I immediately detected a strong odor of an alcoholic beverage emitting from the vehicle. I requested the driver for her license and registration, which she only displayed her license. I was able to identify the driver through her Virginia license as, Norwood, Christel Ebony (1/F, DOB:02/22/1976). While speaking with Norwood, I observed her eyes glassy and her speech slurred. While speaking with Norwood, she then rolls up the front driver side window refusing to speak to me until she found her registration card. I attempted to get her attention by knocking on the window, and she refused to acknowledge me. After multiple attempts to gain Norwood’s attention, I was then able to request for to step out of the vehicle to which she agreed. I asked Norwood if she had consumed any alcoholic beverages, she advised “I consumed one cup of water.” While Norwood stepped out of the vehicle, I noticed her belt was unbuckled, and she buckled her belt before approaching the front of her vehicle.

PRE-ARREST SCREENING (PHASE 3):

Tpr. Sivic #7673 assisted with the traffic stop. I asked Norwood if she knows what city she’s in at the moment, she advised “we’re in Brandywine.”  I asked Norwood are there any medical conditions I should be aware of, she advised “I’m a lot of medication.” I then asked Norwood if she had any head injuries or concussions that I should be aware of, she advised “Yes.” I asked Norwood if it had occurred in the past 24 hours, she advised “Yes, I’ve been banged against the wall. I was actually thinking about going to the doctors tomorrow cause I’m not used to this pain lasting this long.” I asked Norwood if she is a diabetic or had high blood pressure, she advised “Yes” to both. I asked Norwood if she wears glasses or contacts, she advised “Yes” to both. I then asked Norwood if there are any physical disabilities, I should be aware of, she stated “Can I call my family members?” I advised to Norwood we can call after the roadside tests are over. I then asked Norwood to perform Standardized Field Sobriety Test’s (SFST’s), to which she refused to take.

HORIZONTAL GAZE NYSTAGMUS TEST: Refusal.

WALK AND TURN: Refusal.

ONE LEG STAND: Refusal.

Arrest:

-Strong odor of an alcoholic beverage emitting from his breath and person.

-Bloodshot and glassy eyes.

-Slurred and slow speech

-Confused of her surroundings

Norwood was then placed under arrest for Driving under the Influence of Alcohol at 0303 hours. Norwood began to be rude and use derogatory and racial terms towards me. While guiding Norwood to my vehicle, she would not follow any instructions that was given to her. Norwood continuously yelled at me and failed to comply with me while attempting a search incident to arrest. I then attempted to guide Norwood inside the front passenger seat, to which she refused. After asking multiple times for Norwood to have a seat in the vehicle, she finally sat in the vehicle and placed one foot (Left leg) in the vehicle and one foot (Right leg) out the vehicle. I read Norwood her DR-15 Advise of Rights at 0317 hours, and she refused to take the Intoximeter test. While reading the DR-15, Norwood screamed and yelled from when I started reading, until I finished reading. I then asked multiple times for Norwood to place her foot in the vehicle. I then advised Norwood I will assist her on placing her right leg into the vehicle. I lifted and immediately placed her foot in the “A” pillar of my vehicle refusing to let me assist her. I then asked Norwood again to place her foot inside the vehicle and refuse to do so. I then lifted her right foot off the “A” pillar, and she began to lean back on her shoulder blades and scream. I then let go her foot and continued to ask her to place her foot in the vehicle, to which she refused. I then contacted Charles County Sheriff’s Office (CCSO) and requested to a female officer to assist. Once the female officer was on scene, Norwood began to comply. Norwood stated out loud "I do not do drugs, I just drink alcohol" before being transported by CCSO.

Norwood received the following citations:

TA-21-902(a1i) Driving under the influence of alcohol.

TA-21-902(b1i) Driving while impaired by alcohol.

TA-21-901.1(a) Reckless Driving.

TA-21-901.1(b) Negligent Driving.

TA-21-201(a1) Driver failure to obey traffic control device instructions.

TA-21-309(b) Unsafe Lane changing.

TA-21-103(a) Willfully disobeying lawful order/direction of a police officer.

TA-13-409(b) Failure to display registration card.

Norwood was transported to Charles County Detention Center (CCDC) for further processing at 0358 hours. Norwood used racial and derogatory terms towards me while at CCDC.

Norwood was rude and uncooperative the entire process.

All events occurred in Charles County, Maryland.

Case closed.
